name: Priscilla Ricart (Model)
description:
Priscilla Ricart is a Brazilian model and social media star based in Miami. For her TI, I used 25 images taken from her Insta account. After a failed try (using the same parameters as in Maria Guardiola's TI), I changed to a fixed learning rate (of about 0.003) and interrupted the process at only 1615 steps.

This TI has been updated. Please check the "About this version" section!

modelVersions.name: v2.1
modelVersions.description: Actually, I've been testing the 1500-step version and it seems much improved, so I'm uploading this one too. While testing, I've sometimes found results that make me think the TI's on the verge of being overtrained, so I will stop training this model here.

modelVersions.name: v2.0
modelVersions.description: I'm uploading an alternate model that feels more accurate, in my opinion. I've altered my working process a little bit in the last few days. First of all, I don't use the "Use PNG alpha channel as loss weight" anymore, as I felt my embeddings were getting overtrained almost from the start. I have a more active approach now too: I begin with a flat learning rate of around 0.004 and patiently wait until I get some decent pic resembling the subject, which usually doesn't take more than 400 steps anyway. Then I interrupt the process, test the result and reduce the learning rate to maybe 0.001. Run the process for a few more hundred steps and usually I already get a decent TI at least. I guess I'll keep improving the process as I run more tests, but for the time being I'm happy with these results. Hope you like it!
